Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.27,0:01:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,have Nico chant and we'll conclude with personal interviews anybody who wants to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.99,0:01:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,talk to us can we'll give you an individual answer we've got to meet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.69,0:01:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody get to sign anything you want signed just two other things I wanted to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.06,0:01:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,finish off the intellectual history of mankind you see the really decisive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.75,0:01:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectual discussion ended in 350 BC all the rhetoric that you see out about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.82,0:01:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,politics and all it's a good time to review Socrates Plato and and the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.81,0:01:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,greatest thinking throughout mankind I happen to have a set of the great books
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.67,0:01:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Western world it was published in the 30s University of Chicago a world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.81,0:01:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,collection of scholars there is currently a world collection of scholars
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.77,0:01:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that supports the study a true liberal education is to know the great books of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.23,0:02:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the Western world and they suggest you do it over a 10-year period
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.21,0:02:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.03,0:02:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a misspent youth as I have told before the spiritual experiences began
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.95,0:02:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,at age very early age three and age three out of nothingness out of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.02,0:02:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,nothingness out of the oblivion of nothingness suddenly there was a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.44,0:02:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,crashing stunning confrontation with existence I was not pleased not only did
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.27,0:02:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you come back into existence but a body went with it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.92,0:02:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,On top of that stunning fate, the minute there was the awareness of existence, all this happened
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.78,0:03:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,non-verbally.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.78,0:03:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A three-year-old doesn't know such words as existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.23,0:03:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No sooner was there the stunning awareness of existence than instantly there was the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.21,0:03:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,fear of non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.70,0:03:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had come into existence, then it could have been that I would not have come into
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.82,0:03:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,existence and the initial confrontation, the initial duality, polarity was existence versus
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.26,0:03:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,non-existence, whether the infinite reality is void, voidness or allness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.58,0:03:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Having come out of the pathway of negation, each lifetime would end, I would end up in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.94,0:03:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the void because that which you hold in mind is what you experience and if you think the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.24,0:03:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,void is the ultimate reality, that's what you experience is void.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.05,0:03:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if void were the ultimate reality, you could stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.43,0:03:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.01,0:03:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Allness is the ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.43,0:03:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of nothingness, one comes back in to correct it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.53,0:04:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't correct itself to consciousness level 850, transcend the duality of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.41,0:04:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as allness or nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.83,0:04:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes out of a mistranslation of the teaching of the Buddha, no-thingness, emptiness means
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.39,0:04:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,devoid of form, devoid of form, devoid of form.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.27,0:04:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There would be no knowingness of the devoid of form.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.37,0:04:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Of that which is without form, other than consciousness, because without consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.09,0:04:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,what would be knowing the void?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.31,0:04:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the best thinking throughout all of time, which people would like to disregard
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.91,0:04:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in certain, in present society, the best thinkingness of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.55,0:04:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So democracy is built on the best thinkingness of all time and evolved through the French
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.87,0:05:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,philosophers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.87,0:05:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrates around 450, 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.10,0:05:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the best thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.00,0:05:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,460 is excellence, intellectual excellence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.20,0:05:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,One has mastered the physical domain at 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.85,0:05:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see Thomas Aquinas, 460, Aristotle, 498, St. Augustine, 503, you see Chaucer,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.40,0:05:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,480.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.40,0:05:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's Dantès, 455.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.40,0:05:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And Dante, I haven't had a chance to research Dante, how he knew what hell was like, because
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.24,0:05:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,his description of hell was unbelievably accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.26,0:05:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't know how he knew that, but he's at 505, which is rather unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.01,0:06:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see Engels is at 200, Dostoevsky, 465.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.59,0:06:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Descartes is 470.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.39,0:06:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Descartes I refer to in my own writings, because he discerned res interna, from res externa,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.02,0:06:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the subjective from the ostensibly objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.76,0:06:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual work is shifting from perceiving thinking reality as something out there, to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.48,0:06:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,realizing that it is only subjectivity that says there's something out there, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.50,0:06:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,irreducible reality is radical subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.34,0:06:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a very familiar idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.12,0:06:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.86,0:06:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only because I say it is that it has any chance to be is, is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.42,0:06:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, isn't this, you see, is a concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.16,0:06:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't this is a concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.13,0:06:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so Descartes played an extremely important part.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.23,0:06:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwin's theory of evolution we already handled this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.07,0:06:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because at 450 it looks like a dualistic Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.17,0:07:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is also the limitation of theology
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.49,0:07:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which sees God as first cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.53,0:07:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, first cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.55,0:07:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no such thing as first cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.93,0:07:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.33,0:07:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.15,0:07:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.11,0:07:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There ain't no such thing as first cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.96,0:07:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That which always existed can only have a first cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.28,0:07:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, it's trying to project the Newtonian paradigm of cause
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.06,0:07:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to the infinite, nonlinear,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.88,0:07:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which there is no such thing as cause and effect in the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.16,0:07:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Alwaysness has no beginning, so there's no first cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.36,0:07:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To be explained because nothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.54,0:07:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is what it is and it unfolds out of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.40,0:07:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, that's beyond these people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.22,0:07:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we have Euclid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.16,0:07:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got all the great names, Faraday, the great names of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.29,0:08:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see there's a reason we're going to go over this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.57,0:08:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud, you see, stops at 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.27,0:08:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud was limited to the scientific paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.98,0:08:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And I, at one time, was exactly the same place Freud was.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.76,0:08:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,My analysts and myself and Freud, we were all atheists.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.42,0:08:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We all thought religion was foxhole religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.12,0:08:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a fear of dying, now you get God.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.08,0:08:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,See, so we all rejected that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.82,0:08:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so that was a false God that we rejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.60,0:08:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mistake was in assuming,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.80,0:08:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because you've disproven the reality of a false God,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.56,0:08:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that doesn't mean that a true God doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.58,0:08:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.52,0:08:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,where they were thinking that it stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.29,0:08:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You see Galileo at 485.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.41,0:08:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You see Hegel at 425.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.66,0:08:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had to...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.38,0:08:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,For this book, I've had to review all the great philosophers over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.84,0:08:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's really been fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.00,0:09:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like going back to childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.32,0:09:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, other kids were out playing stickball.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.96,0:09:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was sitting there reading Plato and Socrates
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.14,0:09:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and the aphorisms of Marcus Aurelius.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.25,0:09:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.69,0:09:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Little did I realize...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.47,0:09:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that some 70 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.89,0:09:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be what I'd be writing about.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.37,0:09:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What I've been writing about the last couple of months
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.37,0:09:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is what I was reading when I was 12 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.65,0:09:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The dialogues of Plato.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.03,0:09:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.85,0:09:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.73,0:09:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, Gaiety, where they all are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.17,0:09:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The great names of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.53,0:09:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hippocrates, the father of medicine, 485.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.21,0:09:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Homer, the Iliad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.29,0:09:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,William James, the great philosopher Kant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.11,0:09:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Kepler, the great astronomer, Kepler.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.28,0:09:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And Machiavelli.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.81,0:09:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, in the middle of all these incredible people,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.21,0:09:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got Milton, you've got Newton, 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.45,0:10:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got Plato at 485.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.47,0:10:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Plotinus jumps the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.35,0:10:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When you read Plotinus, it's really a spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.55,0:10:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.48,0:10:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You have Sophocles at 485.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.76,0:10:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you've got the great names of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.89,0:10:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Collectively, the greatest minds that ever lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.65,0:10:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's recalibrate the books of the greatest ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.02,0:10:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.54,0:10:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist before the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.80,0:10:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.10,0:10:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Collectively, the great books of the Western world
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.88,0:10:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate over, as they are on the board,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.26,0:10:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate over 460, 465, 470, 475, 470, 475.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.13,0:10:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, if we remove Karl Marx,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.81,0:10:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the great books of the Western world
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.99,0:10:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,will calibrate over 470.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.53,0:10:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,475, 480, 485, 490.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.03,0:10:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.91,0:10:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we have to take Marx out of there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.31,0:10:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a new world, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.28,0:11:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he got in there at 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.36,0:11:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with Marx is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.40,0:11:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that it set up, you know, and gave energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.21,0:11:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,political energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.85,0:11:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to the dualistic concept of perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.71,0:11:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And perpetrator and victim is a poisonous...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.11,0:11:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Perpetrator and victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.25,0:11:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,let's do perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.81,0:11:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The projection of perpetrator and victim
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.15,0:11:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.60,0:11:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates over 130, 135.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.92,0:11:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,135.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.56,0:11:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how perpetrator and victim
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.28,0:11:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is so pervasive in our society
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.26,0:11:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as a sociological, political,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.66,0:11:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,philosophic theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.10,0:11:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's them, society out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.80,0:11:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,causing each thing to be what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.72,0:11:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of seeing each thing is,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.12,0:11:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is because it's radiating forth
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.58,0:11:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,into physicality, its own energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.75,0:12:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That which calibrates at 120
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.43,0:12:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,will live in and create an environment
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.98,0:12:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that is concordant with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.45,0:12:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing is being what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.29,0:12:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its own karmic momentum
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.57,0:12:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and the potentiality coming into actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.27,0:12:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is being caused
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.27,0:12:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,by anything outside of itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.40,0:12:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is being what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.16,0:12:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,By virtue of what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.92,0:12:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Not by virtue of something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.13,0:12:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how serious an error that is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.51,0:12:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in the election.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.39,0:12:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.79,0:12:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.02,0:12:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, there's no karmic responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.30,0:12:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,would there be?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.90,0:12:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all victims of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.75,0:12:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all victims of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.60,0:12:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all victims of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.64,0:12:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all victims of the weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.16,0:12:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all victims of the weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.64,0:13:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all victims of having a physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.82,0:13:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all victims of being human.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.02,0:13:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a victim of getting older.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.87,0:13:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Little people are victims of childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.09,0:13:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to play the victim game,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.17,0:13:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,ad nauseum.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.62,0:13:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Then everything is the victim of everything else
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.14,0:13:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore nothing is responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.80,0:13:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,for its own actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.34,0:13:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is somebody's fault out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.04,0:13:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That justifies vilification,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.78,0:13:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,which justifies,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.44,0:13:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,which justifies hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.72,0:13:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So if by their fruits you shall know them,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.88,0:13:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that distortion of reality
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.88,0:13:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,has a very serious fallout
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.88,0:13:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in my lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.58,0:13:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's caused.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.19,0:13:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Think how many people died
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.19,0:13:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in the various revolutions,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.99,0:13:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.99,0:13:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,World War I, 10 million died
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.99,0:14:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,due to the distortions
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.92,0:14:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.04,0:14:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,World War II, millions more.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.04,0:14:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Chairman Mayo's experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.33,0:14:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Chairman Mayo's experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.36,0:14:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,experiment, experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.81,0:14:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,experiment, cost the lives
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.81,0:14:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of 30 million people who died
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.81,0:14:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.81,0:14:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,30 million people died of starvation
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.81,0:14:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,due to that distortion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.06,0:14:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The vilification of that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.06,0:14:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,which is integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.35,0:14:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions more die.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.20,0:14:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So to be unaware of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.20,0:14:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,serious distortion
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.20,0:14:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,then brings about death
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.20,0:14:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.20,0:14:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we say peace is the automatic
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.20,0:14:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.36,0:14:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,War is the automatic consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.36,0:14:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.36,0:14:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it's cultural war, physical war,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.36,0:14:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or any other kind of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.36,0:14:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.13,0:14:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what we can learn from
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.13,0:15:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.45,0:15:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellectual basis of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.45,0:15:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,democracy then
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.52,0:15:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.52,0:15:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,many centuries old.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.52,0:15:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been refined,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.52,0:15:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,thought about, argued
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.52,0:15:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,by the best minds
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.68,0:15:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.68,0:15:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,For thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.68,0:15:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody has a better
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.51,0:15:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,idea, I'd like to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.51,0:15:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The best
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.73,0:15:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,minds throughout history
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.73,0:15:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,have evolved as
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.73,0:15:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the structure of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.73,0:15:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that we live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.80,0:15:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We live in the highest calibrated country in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.80,0:15:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Highest calibrated country
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.31,0:15:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.31,0:15:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to have
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.31,0:15:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,respect then for that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.31,0:15:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous, calibrated level
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.31,0:15:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,460, 470, 480,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.31,0:15:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that is integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.37,0:15:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That is integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.63,0:15:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So we reverence integrity in all of its forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.63,0:15:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In the snow today
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.63,0:15:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is beauty,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.63,0:16:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and incredible music,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.69,0:16:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and people who devote their lives
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.69,0:16:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to God and to service to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.69,0:16:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We respect beauty because
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.42,0:16:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it is the revelation of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.42,0:16:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, we go
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.25,0:16:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond form itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.86,0:16:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We are no longer dependent
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.86,0:16:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,on the aesthetics of form.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.86,0:16:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We go beyond the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.12,0:16:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,aesthetics of form.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.31,0:16:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And then one sees
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.31,0:16:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,from everything
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.53,0:16:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,radiates divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.53,0:16:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything is equally beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.53,0:16:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You discover that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.66,0:16:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,first in weeds, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.66,0:16:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going by a weed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.66,0:16:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.30,0:16:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,look at this weed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.30,0:16:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an incredible piece of sculpture.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.30,0:16:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Show me any human sculpture
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.30,0:16:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that reaches the perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.30,0:16:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the weed standing there
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.30,0:16:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and its structure is absolutely
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.30,0:16:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,perfect and balanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.30,0:16:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you see
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.52,0:16:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the divinity of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.83,0:17:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we're going to go to a practical
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.81,0:17:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,application of all of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.81,0:17:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,if you think it's just for your spiritual enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.04,0:17:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Or fill up the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.04,0:17:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.04,0:17:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the practicality?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.04,0:17:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is sort of a jump on the book
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.29,0:17:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm finishing up now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.29,0:17:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, every country you can calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.29,0:17:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy level of the people
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.29,0:17:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the government and the leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.29,0:17:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And they can be quite divergent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.32,0:17:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have a very
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.32,0:17:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous people, the people of China.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.32,0:17:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have a seriously pathologic leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.32,0:17:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.48,0:17:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,loving, wonderful people
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.48,0:17:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and their bureaucracy is rotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.55,0:17:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The people are great.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.41,0:17:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The bureaucracy is horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.92,0:17:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There are certain countries you don't drive your own car in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.92,0:17:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because everybody knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.65,0:18:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The slightest thing that happens, they're going to put you in jail
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.65,0:18:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and blackmail your family back home
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.65,0:18:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for 10,000 to get you out of jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.65,0:18:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't drive our car there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.72,0:18:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We leave it at the border.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.87,0:18:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So the leader's integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.87,0:18:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The people are integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.87,0:18:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But the bureaucracy is rotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.03,0:18:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,After the fall of Russian communism,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.03,0:18:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,same thing happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.03,0:18:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The gangsters took over, bureaucracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.32,0:18:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Certain countries in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.32,0:18:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the people are wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.32,0:18:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them have great leaders.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.32,0:18:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But the self-feeding bureaucracy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.32,0:18:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is so rotten through and through
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.32,0:18:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that you don't get integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.32,0:18:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get three different numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.32,0:18:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So diplomacy, when it fails,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.32,0:18:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,costs the lives of millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.32,0:18:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We went back to World War I.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.32,0:18:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We went back to World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.32,0:18:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how each one was due to a failure
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.14,0:18:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of understanding other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.74,0:18:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We antagonized the rest of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.74,0:18:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,by coming on superior
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.74,0:18:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and smugly superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.74,0:19:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to sell them our way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.00,0:19:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the error?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.00,0:19:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it isn't exactly what I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.80,0:19:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another one,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.80,0:19:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but I guess that other one is in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.37,0:19:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have what I call the raw scale
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.37,0:19:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with universal applicability.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.37,0:19:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is, this is called us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.69,0:19:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops, us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.69,0:19:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is called us
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.69,0:19:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is called them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.69,0:19:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you can turn it around.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.69,0:19:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This can be us and that can be them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.69,0:19:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,For convenience, this is us
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.00,0:19:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.45,0:19:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's take it into international diplomacy
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.45,0:19:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and see how we could have prevented
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.45,0:19:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,all the wars that have happened
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.45,0:19:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so far in recent history.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.48,0:19:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We start out, we draw a line.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.48,0:19:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got lines all drawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.48,0:19:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You start out with where are you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.48,0:19:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're at, this is USA, 421.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.48,0:19:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now who do you want to deal with?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.74,0:19:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Who do you want to deal with?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.77,0:19:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to deal with a culture
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.77,0:19:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that is at 225.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.77,0:20:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to sell them your program
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.50,0:20:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of 421
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.50,0:20:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're only at 221
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.50,0:20:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's going to fall on its butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.50,0:20:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not talking the same language.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.50,0:20:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to sell 421
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.01,0:20:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to a country that is at 125.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.24,0:20:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to sell 421
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.24,0:20:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to 125,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.40,0:20:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which is poverty and craving.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.36,0:20:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They care about everybody having a vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.36,0:20:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's an idiotic idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.36,0:20:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people are too dumb to vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.36,0:20:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There's all countries
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.60,0:20:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,where nobody went as far as third grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.60,0:20:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's illiterate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.44,0:20:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Their problem is food.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.44,0:20:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.47,0:20:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Their problem is food.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.47,0:20:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you deal with countries that are run by
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.47,0:20:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,regimes that are run by rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.47,0:20:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so you begin
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.82,0:20:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.26,0:20:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,usefulness of this as a tool.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.26,0:20:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The ones I have at home all have
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.26,0:20:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,little dotted lines with an arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.26,0:20:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have a dotted line.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.26,0:21:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You have your dotted line come down
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.26,0:21:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the arrow goes to whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.26,0:21:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.32,0:21:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This could be your company
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.32,0:21:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is your customer base
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.36,0:21:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're heading for.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.69,0:21:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This could be your advertisement.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.69,0:21:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the group you're heading for?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.69,0:21:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've been calibrating advertisements.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.69,0:21:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, a lot of them make you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.69,0:21:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How they sell whatever they're selling
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.69,0:21:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because every time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.69,0:21:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,there's one pharmaceutical
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.69,0:21:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it's got the most horrible looking woman on the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.69,0:21:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,When you calibrate her, she's 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.69,0:21:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time I open a psychiatric magazine
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.69,0:21:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,there's this ugly looking woman
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.69,0:21:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrating at 130 and I hate their product.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.64,0:21:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate their product.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.64,0:21:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.64,0:21:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So you say
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.83,0:21:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,where are we and where are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.08,0:21:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And now
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.08,0:21:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't make these gross
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.08,0:21:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,miscalculations.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.44,0:21:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There was
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.81,0:22:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Adolf Hitler at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.81,0:22:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,they signed the non-aggression pact.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.48,0:22:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.48,0:22:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Comes back to 110 Downing Street
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.48,0:22:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,peace in our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.09,0:22:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No sooner did he sign this pact with Hitler
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.09,0:22:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll tell you what Hitler was thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.09,0:22:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler was thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.96,0:22:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,what a stupid ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.04,0:22:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He was thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.29,0:22:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,what a stupid ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.39,0:22:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean really.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.32,0:22:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who ever grew up in Chicago
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.32,0:22:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,knows better than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.92,0:22:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The non-aggression pact with
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.46,0:22:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.84,0:22:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute your back is turned
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.84,0:22:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.07,0:22:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's to get you to drop your defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.07,0:22:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The feint.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.13,0:22:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So the non-aggression pact
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.13,0:22:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the inability
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.51,0:22:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to see through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.51,0:23:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.44,0:23:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,try to bring up naivete
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.44,0:23:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.44,0:23:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.44,0:23:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,people with spiritual naivete
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.44,0:23:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,are famous for the blindness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.44,0:23:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of their downside.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.98,0:23:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh everybody's good and sweet
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.98,0:23:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and if we just believe in their goodness and sweetness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.98,0:23:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that's when the truck hits you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.24,0:23:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because that which is against
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.24,0:23:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,where you're at
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.24,0:23:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is looking for an opening
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.24,0:23:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and your blindness is their opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.94,0:23:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,10 million people died
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.94,0:23:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,due to that opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.94,0:23:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're not just talking about theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.39,0:23:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Not talking about theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.39,0:23:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're just good to them
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.39,0:23:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll be good to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.39,0:23:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you what's gonna happen if you're good to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.39,0:23:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And gloat over your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.64,0:23:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.92,0:23:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So to be spiritual doesn't mean to be dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.92,0:23:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't mean to walk around
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.16,0:23:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the world this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.77,0:24:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How did that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.77,0:24:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Try opening this eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.77,0:24:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.89,0:24:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jesus Christ and Krishna
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.89,0:24:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't say it doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.89,0:24:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He said don't go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.89,0:24:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have anything to do with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.89,0:24:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid it. Do not oppose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.89,0:24:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not go to war with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.89,0:24:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't deny it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.28,0:24:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid anything that makes you go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.28,0:24:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.64,0:24:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.67,0:24:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure I don't go weak. Don't go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.80,0:24:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright so
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.24,0:24:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in the book we calibrate the levels
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.34,0:24:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of a number of countries
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.34,0:24:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you see
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.37,0:24:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're dealing with
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.37,0:24:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.37,0:24:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,here's a country
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.37,0:24:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,at a level here
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.37,0:24:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,it's dealing with a country here
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.37,0:24:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot go across this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.37,0:24:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.63,0:25:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.63,0:25:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What was his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.63,0:25:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy that got us into World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.23,0:25:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Chamberlain.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.68,0:25:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You see Chamberlain is coming from
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.68,0:25:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.68,0:25:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he's about 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.71,0:25:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He's around in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.57,0:25:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But look what he's dealing with here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.57,0:25:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's saying
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.57,0:25:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.57,0:25:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.57,0:25:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Look what this guy is.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.02,0:25:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't trust anything below 200
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.02,0:25:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,except that it's going to eat you, kill you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.02,0:25:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or sell you short.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.02,0:25:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright so if he knew beforehand
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.40,0:25:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to meet with a guy
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.40,0:25:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,who calibrates here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.40,0:25:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.14,0:25:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What a different story history would have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.14,0:25:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.49,0:25:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you can use this in relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.49,0:25:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.49,0:25:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Who am I talking to?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.92,0:25:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Where am I? What am I studying?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.92,0:26:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's my business?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.34,0:26:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's my customer base?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.17,0:26:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the university
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.61,0:26:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,where are my students?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.61,0:26:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the professor, where is everybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.61,0:26:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So to talk meaningfully then
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.61,0:26:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,most people that are very
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.45,0:26:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,deviated from truth, far from truth
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.45,0:26:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,are off into sophistry
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.45,0:26:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,rationalization
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.45,0:26:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and rhetoric.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.68,0:26:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We think
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.64,0:26:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're sort of puffed up with pride about it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.64,0:26:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that democracy because it's so superior
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.64,0:26:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and wonderful everybody should just go
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.64,0:26:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,gaga over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.64,0:26:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should they go gaga over that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.79,0:26:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which they don't even understand and don't even
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.79,0:26:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,value?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.11,0:26:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how we antagonize the world to ourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.11,0:26:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.62,0:26:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth of what you are
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.62,0:26:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but how you present that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.62,0:26:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I see the president do the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.62,0:26:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He's thinking that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.62,0:27:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the truthfulness of the content
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.62,0:27:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,should hold the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.62,0:27:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Aristotle said
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.00,0:27:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,aside from
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.54,0:27:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,sophistry there is rhetoric.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.54,0:27:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What's useful about
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.73,0:27:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,rhetoric is the realization that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.73,0:27:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to anticipate where your audience
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.73,0:27:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is at, not just where you're at.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.73,0:27:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to know
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.96,0:27:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,my opinion of Bush's downside
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.96,0:27:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,he knows where he's at
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.96,0:27:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but he doesn't present himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.96,0:27:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't contextualize himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.47,0:27:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So to me most politicians
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.47,0:27:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,are not adept at
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.47,0:27:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,how to contextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.47,0:27:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,where they're coming from.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.47,0:27:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,One simple sentence would
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.94,0:27:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,take them out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.42,0:27:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,conflict they're into.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.42,0:27:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,One simple sentence that would recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.42,0:27:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so they spend all their time defending
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.42,0:27:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves on the level of content
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.42,0:27:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and they contextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.61,0:27:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves with just one or two facts
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.61,0:27:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole field changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.25,0:28:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to defend yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.25,0:28:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth doesn't need to defend itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.54,0:28:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.60,0:28:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the importance of contextualization
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.60,0:28:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is crucial to survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.60,0:28:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Survival of our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.60,0:28:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not just a philosophic position.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.88,0:28:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In your own spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.88,0:28:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's necessary to be able to discern
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.88,0:28:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.01,0:28:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,To avoid getting polarized
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.01,0:28:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in positionalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.01,0:28:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you do is you align
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.01,0:28:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself with the highest truth
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.01,0:28:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are able to recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.01,0:28:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and live your life
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.01,0:28:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in accordance.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.20,0:28:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to give up positionalities
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.20,0:28:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's only
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.20,0:28:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,different ways of looking at
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.20,0:28:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the same phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.20,0:28:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The same phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.81,0:28:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They appear differently
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.81,0:28:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,from two different perspectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.81,0:28:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't mean they're two different realities
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.81,0:28:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.42,0:28:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difficulty with life
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.42,0:29:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in the present world
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.42,0:29:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is that appearance is not essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.41,0:29:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Appearance is not essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.69,0:29:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Appearance is not essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.82,0:29:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That which one is innately
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.82,0:29:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is not what it appears
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.72,0:29:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to be out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.84,0:29:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one of the great values
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.84,0:29:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of calibrating levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.84,0:29:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's why we did
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.88,0:29:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe a thousand for this book
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.88,0:29:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because not everybody is able
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.88,0:29:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to do kinesiology and very often
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.97,0:29:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what we try to do then
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.97,0:29:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is to calibrate the things
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.97,0:29:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of ordinary life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.97,0:29:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual teachers,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.26,0:29:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,religions,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.26,0:29:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,various belief systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.48,0:29:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,various things in our culture,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.48,0:29:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,various architectural styles,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.48,0:29:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the media,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.48,0:29:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,movies, books,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.48,0:29:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,writers, art.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.80,0:29:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We tried to cover the entire
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.80,0:29:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,panorama of human life
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.28,0:29:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and recontextualize it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.28,0:29:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout history.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.41,0:30:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an experience
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.41,0:30:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of its complexities
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.79,0:30:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.84,0:30:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder I'm tired out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.16,0:30:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,God, I wonder
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.78,0:30:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,why I was pooped the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.78,0:30:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.07,0:30:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the Encyclopedia Britannica.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.07,0:30:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course each thing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.07,0:30:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,leads to something interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.07,0:30:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and new.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.07,0:30:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly in the middle
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.07,0:30:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of eating a fork full
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.74,0:30:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of scrambled eggs
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.74,0:30:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you suddenly get,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.74,0:30:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,oh yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.74,0:30:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,valor.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.74,0:30:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Valor is different than curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.74,0:30:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you get what valor means.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.74,0:30:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a whole couple more paragraphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.54,0:30:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see how the book goes on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.54,0:30:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because one thing leads to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.05,0:30:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so we wanted to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.05,0:31:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,have an announcement
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.05,0:31:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.82,0:31:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,have questions and answers
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.82,0:31:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and take a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.82,0:31:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think we tried to cover
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.62,0:31:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that is necessary to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.23,0:31:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not necessary to know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.23,0:31:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we said it today.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.90,0:31:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.90,0:31:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I pledge no thinking, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.41,0:31:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hail to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.80,0:31:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I choose instead to be
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.80,0:31:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that which I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.80,0:31:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I choose to be a prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.80,0:31:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and by my existence
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.80,0:31:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,do I bless thee.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.05,0:31:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,While they're setting up
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.05,0:31:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to have Nico do a chant.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.31,0:31:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotus Sutra.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.00,0:31:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotus Sutra in Sanskrit.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.00,0:31:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's going to do it
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.58,0:32:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,just by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.06,0:32:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And while he's doing that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.06,0:32:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody that has to do anything else
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.38,0:32:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.75,0:32:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Nico.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.75,0:32:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I would suggest just relax into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.16,0:32:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This requires no thinking on your part.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.16,0:32:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And close your eyes if you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.96,0:33:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now we're going to have a chat with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.51,0:33:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.49,0:33:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Michael here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.49,0:33:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm here to see Lord Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.49,0:33:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want to thank you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.49,0:33:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,for your Friendship and for the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.49,0:33:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,support you've shown me over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.49,0:33:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And to make sure you have the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.76,0:33:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,best possible time in your lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.76,0:33:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as you only have one thing to do
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.88,0:33:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I would suggest that we make a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.88,0:33:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible study.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.88,0:33:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this is great to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.14,0:34:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.84,0:35:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.48,0:35:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.87,0:37:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Nico.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.68,0:37:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness, that annoying time between naps.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.20,0:37:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.04,0:38:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.82,0:38:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks very much for everything today.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.62,0:38:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.36,0:38:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Page 304 of your book, you talk about a personal meeting with a sage,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.34,0:38:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're the only one I know, so I came here,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.76,0:38:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't know how it works,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.44,0:38:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but it seems like everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.32,0:38:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,everything else is thinkingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.41,0:38:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you can flare what's going on over there this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.34,0:38:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me embrace you, sir, formally.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.40,0:38:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.64,0:38:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been formally embraced.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.54,0:38:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.32,0:38:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I came.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.42,0:38:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.07,0:38:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.78,0:38:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy's there for...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.50,0:38:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I had a subjective experience recently with meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.44,0:38:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to ask you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.94,0:38:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I closed my eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.26,0:38:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and I did your very simple...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.54,0:38:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I did my very simple thing of looking at the Fahs genes,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.70,0:39:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,looking past them,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.10,0:39:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've waited it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.40,0:39:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually I don't get anything for a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.24,0:39:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and I just sit there for 25 or 30 minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.70,0:39:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and I sat there about that long,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.28,0:39:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there was this ground that materialized.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.30,0:39:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like a sort of a deep space photo,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.26,0:39:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,something like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.20,0:39:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had the sense when I was looking at it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.80,0:39:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was seeing only maybe, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.16,0:39:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,90 degree angle of it or a certain view.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.94,0:39:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I was definitely outside the picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.96,0:39:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I tried to rotate it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.10,0:39:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.22,0:39:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're always talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.50,0:39:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,be the context, be the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.84,0:39:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,be the whole, everything of what you're seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.40,0:39:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tried to rotate it 360,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.08,0:39:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and then suddenly my sense of self,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.76,0:39:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,except for a very thin and persistent pinprick of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.54,0:39:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,like deep in my head,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.16,0:39:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,was like in this field,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.98,0:39:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was no body,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.34,0:39:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,there was nothing at all there
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.46,0:39:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,except the very nagging sensation in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.34,0:39:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm wondering what's going on there,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.68,0:39:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,like,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.02,0:39:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,what level I'm at.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.42,0:39:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't feel bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.92,0:40:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.00,0:40:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually felt like I was led to this point,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.74,0:40:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and I kind of looked back at myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.56,0:40:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and I got the distinct sensation that nothing was there,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.12,0:40:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,like what I consider to be me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.89,0:40:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I was looking back,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.27,0:40:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was like deep space, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.41,0:40:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You became space, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.35,0:40:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.07,0:40:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.21,0:40:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the identification with the content dissolves,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.71,0:40:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to identify with the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.79,0:40:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's why I say spiritual work is really the way you are in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.23,0:40:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you contextualize yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.57,0:40:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you see yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.94,0:40:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to see yourself impersonally.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.77,0:40:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to realize that life is impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.38,0:40:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's subjective,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.00,0:40:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but even the subjective is a quality
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.54,0:40:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that is not a personal possession.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.79,0:41:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening of itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.01,0:41:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is happening of its own,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.86,0:41:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and you stop personalizing it as an I and a that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.44,0:41:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're doing is going into a type of meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.52,0:41:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,where you begin to disidentify with the content,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.22,0:41:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and you become at one with the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.39,0:41:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that you're the field, not the content of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.32,0:41:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That meditative awareness then begins to translate
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.46,0:41:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,into,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.54,0:41:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,into contemplation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.04,0:41:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can experience it intensely in meditation,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.64,0:41:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's the translation into contemplation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.68,0:41:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I recommend contemplation more than meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.74,0:41:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation is very informational.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.16,0:41:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You discover various things,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.88,0:41:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but then as you open your eyes and walk around,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.16,0:42:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the samadhi leaves,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.49,0:42:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're left with what is your
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.95,0:42:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,prevailing level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.35,0:42:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Contemplation is a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.25,0:42:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a supplication to God at all times,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.57,0:42:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to be that which is the expression of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.82,0:42:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,as this form,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.32,0:42:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but then the form only becomes an expression of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.32,0:42:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and it takes the person out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.32,0:42:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So contemplativeness is a way of life, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.48,0:42:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the meditative experience was going from identifying with me,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.80,0:42:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the I,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.80,0:42:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the person itself as content,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.90,0:42:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and experiencing yourself more as context.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.09,0:42:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.41,0:42:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.54,0:42:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.04,0:43:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to your new book.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.78,0:43:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking for it too myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.79,0:43:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You can imagine how cheerful society is about having the truth revealed about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.29,0:43:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean that's what they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.94,0:43:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.74,0:43:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,then leave town several experiences in my life and I shared them with friends
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.88,0:43:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and my husband but I have not been able to talk about them with anyone who could
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.27,0:43:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,really give me a more concrete answer about so many years ago probably eight I
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.39,0:44:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,was working in the library high school library and it was my habit to go there
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.75,0:44:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I was meditating about four hours a day at the time for about three months and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.61,0:44:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd been meditator for about 25 years anyway but I would go and read the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.88,0:44:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Upanishads for about 15 minutes before the students would come so I had this
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.94,0:44:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,quiet time well it got so as I was reading them I was having this
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.64,0:44:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible joy and I understood them not that I could write a comment but I
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.09,0:44:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,understood them on a very wonderful level
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.15,0:44:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.41,0:44:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.45,0:44:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and they gave me so much joy, and I couldn't wait to get in there at lunchtime
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.11,0:44:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,before the students would come and read my panachat.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.46,0:44:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know which one I was on, whether, and I agreed with everything it said, wholeheartedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.18,0:44:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the middle of my reading, there was this experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.56,0:45:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like a veil had opened up.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.06,0:45:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.04,0:45:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The library was gone, everything, and I was in this blackness, such a space.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.16,0:45:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And there were planets and stars coming at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.00,0:45:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I interpreted, that they were light, but I felt I was in the middle of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.64,0:45:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And at first, there was me, but I had completely disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.48,0:45:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, how's all this here in my heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.88,0:45:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.60,0:45:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And from the right side of...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.12,0:45:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,From the left side of me, it said, all this was made by you, for you, and because of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.56,0:45:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.08,0:45:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're in this note today.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.18,0:46:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So I accepted that, and then there was this, it just kept going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.94,0:46:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the planets and the stars kept coming faster and faster at me,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.00,0:46:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as though I was going toward them and they were coming toward me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.62,0:46:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.92,0:46:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How did I get in the middle of the universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.72,0:46:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in a library.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.76,0:46:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So finally, I felt this incredible loneliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.62,0:46:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It was pit, lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.05,0:46:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean, I'm the only one in the universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.97,0:46:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're heading for the void, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.25,0:46:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.31,0:46:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.67,0:46:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I became more lonely and perhaps frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.43,0:46:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, where's God?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.43,0:46:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I wanted to see God, but he wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.99,0:46:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that thought, at the time I was thinking, where's God?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.48,0:46:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This kind of abyss opened up underneath me, at the same time as, and the veil closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.99,0:46:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.35,0:46:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I feel like I blew up.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.63,0:47:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't blow anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.13,0:47:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,For months after that, I lived in a lot of bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.19,0:47:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no ambition.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.55,0:47:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,My desires were all gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.23,0:47:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.55,0:47:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd laugh at rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.11,0:47:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.75,0:47:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.69,0:47:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.17,0:47:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And it faded.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.27,0:47:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.21,0:47:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.61,0:47:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.19,0:47:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.29,0:47:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I blow up?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.21,0:47:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I not go through?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.09,0:47:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I lose my courage?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.65,0:47:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.75,0:47:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,See, where you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.39,0:47:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it really gone forever?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.53,0:47:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Where you were was the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.29,0:47:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you how you know when you're in the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.82,0:47:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference between nothingness and allness is the element of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.48,0:47:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is in.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.50,0:47:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In the allness of divinity, the presence of love is overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.10,0:47:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It melts everything with its infinite grace, its infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.09,0:47:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no feeling of loneliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.91,0:48:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So the loneliness means you're in the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.00,0:48:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was the universe of nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.40,0:48:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's where the pathway of negation will take you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.55,0:48:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There are certain teachings that teach you to negate love.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.85,0:48:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, love is one of the qualities of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.79,0:48:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a serious error.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.74,0:48:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.78,0:48:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who's had a near-death experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.48,0:48:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people here have had a near-death experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.96,0:48:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.24,0:48:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the most telling qualities is you're melted by the exquisiteness of the presence of a love beyond which you've ever even imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.54,0:48:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So you explored the void to see how far it would go.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.09,0:48:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And you found out that it leads to nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.63,0:48:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Loneliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.81,0:48:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.64,0:48:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But you were in a high place to be checking out the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.12,0:49:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.22,0:49:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You were in a very good, you know, advanced stage because of the years of meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.74,0:49:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.23,0:49:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So through the meditation, you were going through the pathway of negation.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.52,0:49:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Not this, not that, not this.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.12,0:49:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So the next step is to realize that divinity is allness, not nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.66,0:49:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.66,0:49:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.30,0:49:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, to understand God, you see, it's through the misunderstanding of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.74,0:49:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,From the ego's viewpoint, love is an attachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.20,0:49:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're going through the pathway of negation, which is let go of attachments and aversions,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.82,0:49:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you would then begin to see love as an attachment and something that would be standing in your way of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.02,0:49:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's emotional attachment on a dualistic basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.98,0:50:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is a quality of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.48,0:50:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.20,0:50:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you negate the reality of love, you will end up in the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.72,0:50:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The totality of divinity includes love, but not dualistic love, a love of a me for a love of a you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.66,0:50:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you leave me, I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.63,0:50:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll own you and possess you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.02,0:50:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see what's the shortcut for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.22,0:50:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Shortcut.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.66,0:50:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the shortcut?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.08,0:50:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I still meditate about the power of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.16,0:50:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I want you to pray to the love of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.80,0:50:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray to the love of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.88,0:50:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.68,0:50:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The pathway of devotional non-duality is non-duality without devotion can lead you into the pathway of negation and bring you to the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.18,0:50:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's the devotion to it that takes you into the divinity of the presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.37,0:51:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence is also without form, but it includes the quality of love which just wipes you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.29,0:51:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It wipes you out in that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.66,0:51:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And the divinity is love and the completeness of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.66,0:51:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difference between the two is the void will take you to a feeling of loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.25,0:51:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite state brings you to a state of completion.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.40,0:51:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In the state of completion, there's nothing you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.80,0:51:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how you can tell a true spiritual teacher from a false one, which is one of the lessons of today.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.08,0:51:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A true teacher needs nothing because a true teacher already is all there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.98,0:51:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If you offer him power, he'd say,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.74,0:51:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What would I do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.22,0:51:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a closet full.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.91,0:51:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be a drag, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.05,0:51:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Control over others, power over others, influence over others.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.75,0:51:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, who would want it?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.50,0:51:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.56,0:52:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fact that it left you incomplete, but the void is a very high space to get into.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.45,0:52:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows a lot of work on your part, more than this lifetime to get that far.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.70,0:52:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, is it coming back?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.68,0:52:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, my life after...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.64,0:52:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless God hates you, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.52,0:52:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You pissed me off, girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.86,0:52:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess because it faded, because I lived for three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.58,0:52:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a stunning space to be in.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.44,0:52:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very, very stunning space.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.22,0:52:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,To the naive person, they think this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.08,0:52:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it has all the qualities of a finale, there's a finality to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.74,0:52:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something about it that is the ultimate.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.38,0:52:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.88,0:52:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the ultimate void.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.16,0:52:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not necessarily where I want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.64,0:52:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not where you want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.24,0:52:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to go to allness rather than nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.78,0:52:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.58,0:52:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,At age three, I looked at that at age three.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.50,0:52:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.16,0:53:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,At age three, that was the confrontation.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.92,0:53:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Allness versus nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.84,0:53:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Existence versus non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.72,0:53:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So devotion would be the...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.58,0:53:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, pray to the love of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.18,0:53:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray to the love of God, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.98,0:53:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is where I started when I was a teenager.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.74,0:53:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.02,0:53:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Just hanging with love.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.70,0:53:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Just hanging with the love of God, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.82,0:53:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You've done enough of the not this and not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.36,0:53:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I did a lot of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.86,0:53:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You already know you're not this and not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.56,0:53:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I did that a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.78,0:53:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all that is, so now just be inclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.14,0:53:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.46,0:53:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.32,0:53:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So divinity is exquisitely beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.84,0:53:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's exquisite beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.66,0:53:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's exquisite gentleness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.68,0:53:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's loving to the point that you feel like you could melt in it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.24,0:53:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and die this moment and you would be complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.54,0:53:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.48,0:53:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You know you're there.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.34,0:53:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When if you're suddenly expired, it would be perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.14,0:53:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.48,0:53:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.94,0:53:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're already complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.80,0:53:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing more you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.12,0:53:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.02,0:53:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.98,0:53:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.46,0:53:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for answering.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.92,0:54:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.17,0:54:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it wasn't because for like eight years I feel like I've been...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.03,0:54:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.25,0:54:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very stunning space to be in.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.11,0:54:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The void is a very stunning space.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.53,0:54:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like I've been in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.85,0:54:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you were suffering from void shock for a number of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.55,0:54:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.95,0:54:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.03,0:54:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.07,0:54:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.09,0:54:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.11,0:54:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.17,0:54:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.23,0:54:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.25,0:54:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.31,0:54:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.41,0:54:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.49,0:54:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.55,0:54:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.61,0:54:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.65,0:54:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.71,0:54:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.73,0:54:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.79,0:54:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.85,0:54:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.97,0:54:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.01,0:54:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.07,0:54:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.11,0:54:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.15,0:54:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.17,0:54:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.19,0:54:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.21,0:54:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.31,0:54:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.53,0:54:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that's a...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.53,0:54:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it's a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.29,0:54:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.65,0:54:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.43,0:54:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And it leaves you shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.93,0:54:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.99,0:54:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He was with me through this whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.09,0:54:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you feel shocked like you have somehow failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.23,0:54:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.11,0:54:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.39,0:54:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.57,0:54:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like I blew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.41,0:54:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.77,0:54:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You feel like you blew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.81,0:54:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.47,0:54:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the space is very, very impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.11,0:54:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.27,0:54:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.57,0:54:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,God is space.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.49,0:54:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was like...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.79,0:54:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.67,0:54:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Being part of our space.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.95,0:54:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond form.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.05,0:54:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.09,0:54:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond location.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.41,0:54:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond personal identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.41,0:54:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I shouldn't read the punishments anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.95,0:54:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I love reading them.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.13,0:54:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, they give my heart joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.65,0:54:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You just do what I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.13,0:54:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.55,0:54:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.07,0:54:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll start.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.94,0:55:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's my teddy bear?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.56,0:55:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Your teddy bear?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.46,0:55:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I need my teddy bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.72,0:55:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.92,0:55:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,She scared me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.66,0:55:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I need my teddy bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.82,0:55:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see, you meditate on the purr of a kitty and a dog's wagging tail, and it'll
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.69,0:55:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,take you from nothingness to happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.45,0:55:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll take you from nothingness to almas.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.97,0:55:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.35,0:55:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I have a question about God and consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.11,0:55:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's your teddy bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.19,0:55:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, teddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.95,0:55:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I was frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.63,0:55:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That lady frightened me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.04,0:55:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We're okay, teddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.62,0:55:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We're okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.24,0:55:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Are God and consciousness the same thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.78,0:55:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Or what is their relation?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.80,0:55:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.28,0:55:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to write and talk to you at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.36,0:55:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Experientially, out of the unmanifest arises the manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.08,0:56:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the manifest arises the manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.98,0:56:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the manifest arises the manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.40,0:56:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the manifest arises consciousness, which is not different than the energy of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.33,0:56:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The light energy of consciousness, life, when it interacts with material matter, spawns
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.33,0:56:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,living, biologic life as we know it throughout evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.98,0:56:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is without form.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.08,0:56:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's within the subjective experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.49,0:56:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.59,0:56:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So that would be God manifest to the degree...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.84,0:56:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That is, God as divinity is subjectively experiential as self with a capital S, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.86,0:57:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Totally unmanifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.50,0:57:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There would be no capacity for knowing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.08,0:57:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.56,0:57:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's my right arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.59,0:57:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Right arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.64,0:57:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, she's hiding behind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.46,0:57:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.83,0:57:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That which was just expressed was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.81,0:57:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.87,0:57:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd never said that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.39,0:57:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you repeat it, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.93,0:57:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.63,0:57:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.79,0:57:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Total consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.94,0:57:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity is infinite potentiality, omnipotent.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.00,0:57:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Omnipotent, omniscient, omnipresent.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.52,0:57:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.46,0:57:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the God, the Godhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.14,0:58:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the Godhead manifests God as creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.74,0:58:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's only an actualization of a potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.16,0:58:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The unmanifest is not bound to become manifest, but out of its potentiality becomes manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.01,0:58:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,as the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.91,0:58:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Within the universe, then, is born the capacity for consciousness and awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.84,0:58:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The manifestation of God as consciousness, then, is one of the manifestations of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.24,0:58:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,which we share with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.10,0:58:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.10,0:58:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.35,0:58:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence of God within us is knowable by virtue of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.67,0:58:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the expression of God as consciousness, you would not even know that you exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.32,0:59:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,To be aware that you are is already an expression of divinity as consciousness is experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.77,0:59:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in the subjective.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.77,0:59:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,To say, to be aware that you are, to know that you are, to say it is taking you out
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.36,0:59:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.36,0:59:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.58,0:59:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.58,0:59:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.32,0:59:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.32,0:59:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than believing, it's knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.32,0:59:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because even to use an intransitive verb like am-ness is already a step down from
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.00,0:59:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.00,0:59:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If you calibrate the statement I am, it's less than the ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.24,0:59:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is is beyond all categories, such as beingness, existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.68,0:59:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Am-ness is an intransitive verb, but it's a denigration of the level of the true state.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.75,1:00:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.16,1:00:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for asking me such a fun question.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.16,1:00:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.16,1:00:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I sign them all?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.85,1:00:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.85,1:00:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.80,1:00:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There are some Lollapaloozas in the audience, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.02,1:00:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't ask you dumb things.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.02,1:00:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.02,1:00:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.02,1:00:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.02,1:00:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.02,1:00:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I would just like to thank you for all your sharing.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.02,1:00:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your sharing.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.02,1:00:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.02,1:00:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And your giving.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.28,1:00:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the most generous teacher I've ever known.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.28,1:00:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nobody there to be generous.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.61,1:00:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.61,1:00:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.61,1:00:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.61,1:00:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.61,1:00:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.61,1:00:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.61,1:00:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.61,1:00:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.61,1:00:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.35,1:00:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.35,1:00:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.35,1:00:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.64,1:00:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.64,1:01:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But nobody there to be generous.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.64,1:01:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Its just a condition.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.64,1:01:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If I an anything to do it, I'll be stingy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.83,1:01:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Wake up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.31,1:01:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the bear?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.07,1:01:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the king?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.19,1:01:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He's listening in.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.79,1:01:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He's eavesdropping.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.91,1:01:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks that's a microphone dumbbell.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.21,1:01:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the wrong end.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.21,1:01:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.27,1:01:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.59,1:01:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You see-
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.94,1:01:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.15,1:01:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A sense of humor is necessary to existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.68,1:01:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a sense of humor, you can't really get along spiritually, I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.08,1:01:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because humor is the capacity to go outside yourself and laugh at yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.16,1:01:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You laugh at yourself, you're forgiving yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.14,1:01:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You're including yourself in and letting it be okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.26,1:01:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So the humor of human life is a way of healing.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.54,1:02:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You can laugh at yourself well, you see, because everything's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.75,1:02:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is a theater of the absurd.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.85,1:02:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you read the daily headlines, you realize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.88,1:02:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's madness, you say, I really don't believe this.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.54,1:02:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Get some guy on TV, you say, I can't believe this is happening.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.48,1:02:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Theater of the absurd.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.83,1:02:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's comical.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.72,1:02:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Some spiritual teacher that used to teach me.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.18,1:02:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.10,1:02:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a serious error to take life seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.46,1:02:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I think taking life seriously is comical.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.34,1:02:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to get serious about taking life as being comical.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.10,1:02:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Farrah, yeah, golly, whiz.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.33,1:03:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.83,1:03:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't have a story, I don't have a question, and if you knew me two years
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.27,1:03:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,ago, you'd know.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.59,1:03:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You would know what a miracle that is.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.47,1:03:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, great.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.47,1:03:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Great.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.47,1:03:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've been through some kind of wondrous transformation, I can see, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.16,1:03:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I can't even speak, see, that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.44,1:03:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.44,1:03:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.44,1:03:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not explicable.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.94,1:03:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not explicable.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.94,1:03:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a condition.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.13,1:03:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a condition that prevails.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.75,1:03:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why nobody goes through it takes credit for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.30,1:03:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody becomes egoistic about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.30,1:04:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody becomes egoistic or prideful because it is not of the personal self.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.71,1:04:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,One is the recipient of the benefit of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.33,1:04:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.45,1:04:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's terrific.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.54,1:04:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.54,1:04:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She's referring him up, so if she wants...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.54,1:04:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.64,1:04:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody has to come up.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.64,1:04:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be happy to sign their books incognito.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.26,1:04:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Ben Lawden.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.42,1:04:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He tried to get my autograph on a book.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.95,1:04:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's not me.
